  "prompt": "Who is Nira Radia and what did she actually do?",
  "response": "Nira Radia is an Indian public relations consultant and lobbyist who gained significant media attention in India for her involvement in a major political and corporate scandal that came to light in late 2010. She was the central figure in what became known as the \"Radia tapes\" controversy, which involved a series of recorded phone conversations that were leaked to the media.\n\nThe conversations, which were reportedly intercepted by authorities, suggested that Radia was engaged in influencing political figures, journalists, and other individuals in relation to various business interests and lobbying efforts. The tapes revealed discussions about the allocation of 2G spectrum licenses, a telecom scandal that involved high-profile politicians and significant financial irregularities. The recordings also indicated attempts to manipulate media coverage in favor of certain corporate entities.\n\nThe scandal raised questions about the nexus between business, media, and politics in India, leading to widespread public debate and scrutiny. It resulted in investigations by law enforcement agencies and substantial media reporting, affecting several prominent individuals and organizations.\n\nRadia's case highlighted issues of ethics in lobbying and public relations, as well as the relationships between business leaders and government officials in India. The fallout from the controversy had lasting implications for corporate governance and accountability in the country.",
